quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  2,1,"Alif Lām Mīm."
  2,2,"That is the Scripture; there is no doubt about it—a guidance for the mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>,{1}",footnotes:1:This portion can be read differently in Arabic by pausing after ‘doubt’, and in this case it means: ‘That is the Scripture, no doubt. In it there is guidance for the mindful (of God).’
  2,3,"who believe in the<i class=""s"">(existence of) </i>hidden realms and establish the prayers and spend out of what We have provided them,"
  2,4,"and those who believe in what has been sent down to you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>and what has been sent down before you, and regarding the Hereafter they are certain."
  2,5,"Those are upon guidance from their Lord, and those are the successful."
